<center>
<h3>
Is a Point in a Box?
</h3>
</center>
<hr WIDTH="100%">
<h2>Introduction:</h2>
This lab exercises the ability to:
<ul>
    <li> Work with conditionals (<i>primary</i>) </li>
    <li> Work with coordinate geometry (<i>secondary</i>) </li>
</ul>
<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

<ol>
    <li> Create a new Webpage in a new folder, <i>lab9</i>, and move to it.</li>
    <li> Determine whether a given point's (X,Y) coordinate pair is in a specified box area, using the following components:</li>
    <ul>
	<li>Textboxes (<i>with default values</i>) for each of the [input] values of the box coordinates:
	<b>Top, Bottom, Left, and Right.</b>
	<li><tt><u>alert</u>()</tt> the user to the following input errors: <b>Top &le; Bottom</b> and/or <b>Left &ge; Right.</b>
	<li>Two labeled textboxes for the (<i>X,Y</i>) coordinates of the point, i.e.
	    a textbox for the <i>X</i> coordinate, and a textbox for the <i>Y</i> coordinate.
	<li>A labeled button to <i>toggle</i> whether the box border is considered to be in the box. (<i>Establish and use a default value</i>)<br>
	This button will toggle a Boolean <i>flag</i> variable. This button will also use a textbox to display one of the following two text strings (messages) on the page in a textbox:<br>
	<dl>
	    <dt>
		<b><tt>true</tt></b>
	    <dd>
		<tt>The box border is <b>inside</b> the box.</tt>
	    <dt>
		<b><tt>false</tt></b>
	    <dd>
		<tt>The box border is <b>outside</b> the box.</tt>
	</dl>
	<li>A button to test whether or not the point is in the box.
	<li>A textbox to display and state whether the point is in the box, e.g.:
	<dl>
	    <dt>
		<b><tt>true</tt></b>
	    <dd>
	    <tt>The point ( <b><i>X</i></b>, <b><i>Y</i></b> ) is <b>inside</b> the box.</tt>
	    <dt>
		<b><tt>false</tt></b>
	    <dd>
	    <tt>The point ( <b><i>X</i></b>, <b><i>Y</i></b> ) is <b>outside</b> the box.</tt>
	    <dd>
	    <br>(<b>note:</b> <i>display the values of X and Y</i>)
	</dl>
    </ul>
</ol>

<p>Label descriptively all boxes and buttons (a table might be in order).
<p><u>Test</u> your code.
<p>Try to use functions to help organize and simplify your code.
<p>When finished, submit to the dropbox.

